- Expected on Jetson and some devices: you may see
  "wgpu DRM surface create failed: ... Failed to find suitable drm device". This is normal when the driver lacks the Vulkan direct-display extensions or has split GPU/display DRM devices. The app will automatically switch to the CPU KMS scanout fallback, and you should see the animated triangle.

- Stop with Ctrl+C (or ESC if built with the esc_evdev feature).

### 5.5 Feature flags
- wgpu_drm: Enables the direct Vulkan→DRM surface path in wgpu.
- kms_cpu_scanout: Enables the CPU fallback path: offscreen wgpu render → CPU readback → RGBA→XRGB8888 → KMS dumb-buffer blit with double-buffered page flips.
- esc_evdev: Optional ESC key listener via evdev to exit cleanly (adds evdev dependency; requires membership in the input group).

